ce:section.ce:para:
The effect of CQDs on the total length and growth rate of larvae was evaluated during the studied period. The treated larvae with all of the CQDs showed a negative effect on the growth rates, which were significantly reduced by increasing the concentration of CQDs at 96 hpf (Fig. 4
                           ). Arguably, the higher the toxicity of CQDs the greater the reduction in the growth rate recorded. In like manner, a reduction in the total body length was observed for the exposed zebrafish larvae as compared with the control group. This decrease in length, also, holds true among the CQD-treated zebrafish (p < 0.05). For the non-doped CQDs, the total length was largely affected by the time (F = 1668.614; P < 0.001) and concentration of exposure (F = 299.332; P < 0.001) and also by the interaction of time and concentration (F = 2.927; P = 0.01), as shown in Fig. 4 
                           .Likewise, for N-doped CQDs the total length was largely affected by both, time (F = 1066.356; P < 0.0001) and concentration (F = 173.295; P < 0.0001). Finally, for N,S-co-doped CQDs, the length was affected by the time F = 310.190; P < 0.001) and concentration (F = 209.174; P < 0.001) as well as by the interaction of time and concentration (F = 11.31; P < 0.001).
